Methods in Java - block of code that performs certain actions

Built-in methods - string.length -> returns the number of characters in a string

Methods:
      - with parameters
      - without parameters

create a method to return the results of adding the numbers

    public double addNumbers(double num1, double num2){
    return  num1+num2;
    }

Must have parts in methods:
    1) return type (we can return any type - eg, primitive or non primitive or void)
    2) name of the method
    3) parameters/no parameters

Benefits of methods:
    1) reduces the code duplication
    2) cleaner code
    3) makes the code manageable
    4) save memory
    5) increases readability

Variables:
    1) Local
        - any variable that is declared inside a method or a block or a constructor
    2)